    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>29 March 5619</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">If not too late please send<lb/> with the <date>March</date>
                Occidents three copies<lb/> of your Daily Prayers—Two of the larger<lb/> 8 mo size
                &amp; 1 of the 12 mo. edition. If<lb/> too late for the <date>March</date>
                Occidents, and you<lb/> have no other opportunity, the parties<lb/> wanting them
                might wait till <date>April</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am much engaged just now<lb/> and have no leisure to write you at
                any<lb/> length. I have a lecture to prepare for<lb/> the natural history society
                who have<lb/> lately moved in a fine new building<lb/> In witness whereof I have
                sent you a<lb/> circular wherein you may see I am<lb/> booked for next week. The
                opening was<lb/> a very pleasant occasion.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I trust to have the pleasure<lb/> of writing you soon and with
                best<lb/> wishes for your health and welfare<lb/> Please hand enclosed to<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Wm Florance</persName>. I am<lb/> sincerely sorry for his and <hi
                    rend="underline">your</hi> loss.<lb/> Have you any numbers<lb/> of the Asmonean
                you<lb/> would feel disposed<lb/> to part with to complete<lb/> a set.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">I am Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">INAUGURATION</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OF</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The New Building</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OF THE</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>MONTREAL</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">NATURAL HISTORY SOCIETY,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, FEB. 22, 1859</date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">——————</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Museum will be opened at Seven</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">o'clock, and the Chair will be taken by</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">PRINCIPAL <persName>DAWSON</persName>, President of the
                Society,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">AT EIGHT O'CLOCK, PRECISELY.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">ADDRESSES ARE EXPECTED FROM</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">HIS EXCELLENCY <persName>SIR WM. EYRE</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>PROFESSOR HALL</persName> OF
                    <placeName>ALBANY</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE <persName>LORD BISHOP</persName> OF
                    <placeName>MONTREAL</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE <persName>HON. P.O. CHAUVEAU</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE <persName>HON. JUDGE AYLWIN</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>DR. HOLMES</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <persName>F. G. JOHNSON, ESQ.</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">——————</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Several Pieces of Music will be performed</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">during the Evening.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <emph rend="italics">Recess for Promenade and Conversation</emph>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <emph rend="italics">from 9 to half past 9. </emph>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">COFFEE, &amp;c., by <persName>Mr. Chas.
                ALEXANDER</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">TICKETS,—Gentleman's, 2s 6d; Lady's, 2s 6d,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">including Refreshments.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><persName>JOHN LEEMING</persName>, Rec. Sec.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>Henry Rose, Printer.    [OVER.]</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Winter Course of Lectures,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">WHICH ARE</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">FREE TO THE PUBLIC,</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">WILL BE DELIVERED AS FOLLOWS:</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> March</date>—Introductory
                Lecture by the President.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March</date>—By <persName
                    role="author">Rev. Dr. DeSola</persName>—Subject, “Scripture Zoology.”</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March</date>—By
                    <persName>W. H. Hingston, M. D.</persName>—Subject, “Climate<lb/> of
                    <placeName>Canada</placeName>.”</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>
                    March</date>—<persName>By Rev. A. F. Kemp</persName>—Subject, “Fresh Water
                Algae.”</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March</date>—By
                    <persName>Professor S. P. Robins</persName>—Subject, “Force.”</p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><date>TUESDAY, 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> April</date>—By the
                    <persName>Lord Bishop</persName>—Subject, “State and Prospects of<lb/> Science
                and Literature in <placeName>Montreal</placeName>.”</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Lectures commence each evening at EIGHT o'clock.</p>
            <p/>
            <p rend="align(center)">The following are the</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">OFFICERS OF THE NATURAL HISTORY SOCIETY.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">FOR THE YEAR <date>1859</date>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">PRINCIPAL
                    <persName>DAWSON</persName>,.....................................<emph
                    rend="italics">President.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName role="author">REV. A.
                    DESOLA</persName>.................................1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>
                <emph rend="italics">Vice President.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">THE <persName>LORD
                    BISHOP</persName>,...................................2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>
                <emph rend="italics">Vice President.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>E. BILINGS</persName>,
                    Esq.,.......................3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>
                <emph rend="italics">Vice President.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>JAS. FERRIER, JR., Esq.</persName>,.................
                    <emph rend="italics">Treasurer.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>W. H. HINGSTON, M.
                    D</persName>...............................<emph rend="italics">Cor.
                    Secretary.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)"><persName>JOHN
                LEEMING</persName>,................................. <emph rend="italics">Rec.
                    Secretary.</emph></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Annual Subscription to the Society is $4 and one dollar
                entrance and<lb/> diploma.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Persons desirous of becoming Members will please apply to any of
                the<lb/> Officers of the Society.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">The Canadian Naturalist, a bi-monthly Magazine is issued under
                the</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">auspices of the Society, price $3 per annum, published by
                    <persName>B. Dawson &amp; Sons</persName>.</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March 59</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Parcel of<lb/> Asmoneans Prayers &amp; Occidents duly<lb/> came
                to hand. For former receive<lb/> my thanks. The nos only contained<lb/> two I
                required, should you have<lb/> any more turning up at this<lb/> time of
                    <add>Hebrew</add> post them s. a. p.<lb/> instead of learning them. I only
                write<lb/> you now to advise you to send<lb/> in several extra copies of your<lb/>
                No 1 new series, as it is only by<lb/> sending them out extensively that<lb/> I can
                hope to get you new subscribers.<lb/> I have already given more to <persName>Mr<lb/>
                    Abm Joseph</persName> of <placeName>Quebec</placeName> who happened</p>
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p>to be here. He will subscribe, to<lb/> send him direct his nos. I mailed<lb/> for you
                the nos. you requested.<lb/> We have of course to prepay<lb/> one cent postage from
                one part<lb/> of the Province to the other. I will<lb/> endeavor to make some
                collections<lb/> for you in <date>Medianos Pesach</date>.<lb/> Tell them I am pretty
                well engaged.<lb/> Wishing you <add>Hebrew</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">I am yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p>You had better send in<lb/> your extra copies of No 1 by mail.</p>
        </body>
